          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Relative High Energy Neutron Yields from Targets",
                "Bombarded with Protons and Deuterons"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "AUTHOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "W.J.Knox"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "REFERENCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "code": "J,PR,81,687,1951",
                "code_unit": [
                  {
                    "unit": "J,PR,81,687,1951",
                    "doi": "10.1103/PhysRev.81.687",
                    "field": {
                      "reference_type": "J",
                      "reference": {
                        "code": "PR",
                        "number": null,
                        "volume": "81",
                        "part": null,
                        "issue": null,
                        "page": "687"
                      },
                      "date": 1951
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "unit_combination": "(%)"
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "#doi:10.1103/PhysRev.81.687"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INSTITUTE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "1USABRK"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "CYCLO"
                ],
                "institute": "1USABRK"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The 184-inch Berkeley cyclotron."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The deuterons produced by the cyclotron have",
                "a maximum energy of 190 MeV, and a beam of about",
                "10**-6-amp average current can be obtained. The",
                "protons have a maximum energy of 340 MeV and can be",
                "produced with an average beam current of the order of",
                "5*10**-7 amp."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "FISCH",
                "GEMUC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Bi fission chamber."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Bismuth fission chambers were used to detect the high",
                "energy neutrons. Graphite monitors were used to",
                "determine the fluxes of protons or deuterons",
                "traversing the targets. The monitors were attached to",
                "the target so that the beam passed, simultaneously,",
                "through both target and monitor. At the end of the",
                "bombardment the monitor was removed and the counting",
                "rate of the C11 activity in it was determined on a",
                "Geiger-Mueller counter at a suitable later time.",
                "Sometimes decay curves were taken through an aluminum",
                "absorber so that the positron annihilation radiation",
                "of the C11 was counted instead of the positrons",
                "themselves."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "DECAY"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The relative neutron yield from a given",
                "element was obtained by comparison of its corrected",
                "neutron yield to the yield from a standard carbon",
                "target. The estimated probable error of a single",
                "determination of such a ratio is about 10 percent.",
                "This error arises mainly in the determination of the",
                "flux of deuterons or protons traversing a target, but",
                "also has contributions from the neutron counting",
                "statistics and from the correction made for the",
                "production of neutrons in the carbon monitors. The",
                "errors in measurements of the thicknesses and",
                "densities of the targets are negligible."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "For each of the four targets used in a given run, the",
                "neutron counting rate was determined and corrected",
                "for the neutrons produced in the monitors and the",
                "relative neutron yields for the four targets were",
                "calculated."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "HISTORY": [
